00:16:57.016 --> 00:17:00.019 align:middle line:84%
Now, see, whenever I talk
about that, I get chills.

00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:01.395 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: You get
chills on that.

00:17:01.395 --> 00:17:05.191 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Because fundamentally
stop and think about-- now,

00:17:05.191 --> 00:17:09.528 align:middle line:84%
we have people out there
doing the work of our country

00:17:09.528 --> 00:17:10.988 align:middle line:84%
that we've determined
to have done.

00:17:10.988 --> 00:17:12.990 align:middle line:84%
And whether we agree with
it or not, these people, men

00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.032 align:middle line:90%
and women--

00:17:14.032 --> 00:17:15.117 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Putting their
lives on the line.

00:17:15.117 --> 00:17:16.410 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: These are
our sons and daughters.

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:17.869 align:middle line:84%
These are our
brothers and sisters.

00:17:17.869 --> 00:17:19.329 align:middle line:90%
These are people we care about.

00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:20.498 align:middle line:90%
And so they go into combat.

00:17:20.498 --> 00:17:21.707 align:middle line:90%
They experience these things.

00:17:21.707 --> 00:17:26.337 align:middle line:84%
And maybe they do some things
that they shouldn't have done.

00:17:26.337 --> 00:17:28.547 align:middle line:90%
Should we wipe memory out?

00:17:28.547 --> 00:17:29.966 align:middle line:90%
Is that the real solution?

00:17:29.966 --> 00:17:31.759 align:middle line:84%
And what memories do
we decide to wipe out?

00:17:31.759 --> 00:17:34.387 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I was going to
