can exert force on his capsule.

00:28:28.165 --> 00:28:30.876 align:middle line:84%
And inside your body,
this can be navigated.

00:28:30.876 --> 00:28:33.337 align:middle line:84%
So it can roll
inside your stomach.

00:28:33.337 --> 00:28:34.671 align:middle line:90%
It can be stopped.

00:28:34.671 --> 00:28:38.467 align:middle line:84%
It can go backward and
forward as a robot.

00:28:38.467 --> 00:28:41.011 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, how would
you put it in you?

00:28:41.011 --> 00:28:41.887 align:middle line:90%
>> So you swallow it.

00:28:41.887 --> 00:28:42.804 align:middle line:90%
So it's a pill size.

00:28:42.804 --> 00:28:43.597 align:middle line:90%
>> You swallow it?

00:28:43.597 --> 00:28:44.389 align:middle line:90%
>> So, yeah.

00:28:44.389 --> 00:28:48.185 align:middle line:84%
This is completely mindless
robot, as you see in the video.

00:28:48.185 --> 00:28:52.314 align:middle line:84%
It's made out of a soft
material so that it can deform,

00:28:52.314 --> 00:28:54.608 align:middle line:84%
and it's very safe to
use, as you mentioned.

00:28:54.608 --> 00:28:57.194 align:middle line:84%
Safety is our first
rule about the design.

00:28:57.194 --> 00:29:01.156 align:middle line:84%
And by rolling inside your
stomach's tissue surface,

00:29:01.156 --> 00:29:02.866 align:middle line:90%
the doctor can stop it.

00:29:02.866 --> 00:29:05.077 align:middle line:84%
And then by controlling
the external force,

00:29:05.077 --> 00:29:06.578 align:middle line:90%
you can indeed eject a drug.

00:29:06.578 --> 00:29:08.413 align:middle line:84%
Here you see this blue
thing is [INAUDIBLE].

00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:08.538 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, wow.

00:29:08.538 --> 00:29:10.582 align:middle line:84%
It spilled-- it made
little pee or something.

00:29:10.582 --> 00:29:12.209 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:12.209 --> 00:29:13.251 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:29:13.251 --> 00:29:15.796 align:middle line:90%
And it can do this many times.

00:29:15.796 --> 00:29:18.882 align:middle line:84%
And it can actively
image your body

00:29:18.882 --> 00:29:22.427 align:middle line:84%
so that you can see
where you want exactly.

00:29:22.427 --> 00:29:24.554 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: What an amazing
little tiny machine.

00:29:24.554 --> 00:29:25.055 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Right.

00:29:25.055 --> 00:29:27.307 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to see them
get smaller and smaller.

00:29:27.307 --> 00:29:29.476 align:middle line:84%
And this is, again, the
nature of the technology.

00:29:29.476 --> 00:29:32.020 align:middle line:84%
And when you think about the
convergence of technology,

00:29:32.020 --> 00:29:34.022 align:middle line:84%
nanotechnologies that
take devices and make

00:29:34.022 --> 00:29:36.650 align:middle line:84%
them very small-- when
you take computing

00:29:36.650 --> 00:29:39.486 align:middle line:84%
power as an example and
the speed of computing--

00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:41.196 align:middle line:84%
and this is the big
change that's coming.

00:29:41.196 --> 00:29:44.282 align:middle line:84%
This is where all of it falls
into a whole other niche,

00:29:44.282 --> 00:29:47.202 align:middle line:84%
is when you think about
supercomputing today, we

00:29:47.202 --> 00:29:50.789 align:middle line:84%
do I think 280, 300
teraflops a second,

00:29:50.789 --> 00:29:53.041 align:middle line:84%
which is like
everybody on the planet

00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:57.671 align:middle line:84%
with a calculator for 60 hours
doing calculations in a second.

00:29:57.671 --> 00:30:02.968 align:middle line:84%
Now, the computers
that are coming

00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:07.639 align:middle line:84%
will do what a supercomputer
does in a trillion years in one

00:30:07.639 --> 00:30:08.598 align:middle line:90%
hour.

00:30:08.598 --> 00:30:09.725 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: In one an hour.

00:30:09.725 --> 00:30:10.308 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: In one hour.

00:30:10.308 --> 00:30:10.684 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Amazing.

00:30:10.684 --> 00:30:13.020 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Now, this changes
everything about everything.

00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:15.564 align:middle line:84%
Because whoever reaches
that threshold first,

00:30:15.564 --> 00:30:17.774 align:middle line:90%
encryption becomes obsolete.

00:30:17.774 --> 00:30:18.567 align:middle line:90%
Boom.

00:30:18.567 --> 00:30:20.527 align:middle line:84%
Because that amount
of computing power

00:30:20.527 --> 00:30:22.946 align:middle line:84%
can rip anything
apart as far as-- when

00:30:22.946 --> 00:30:24.698 align:middle line:84%
you think about
controlling-- whoever

00:30:24.698 --> 00:30:28.535 align:middle line:84%
gets there first-- whoever
gets there first on quantum

00:30:28.535 --> 00:30:30.704 align:middle line:90%
computing wins.

00:30:30.704 --> 00:30:34.082 align:middle line:84%
Because you have control of
every electromagnetic system

00:30:34.082 --> 00:30:36.668 align:middle line:84%
that has an entry point
through a data point.

00:30:36.668 --> 00:30:38.754 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Has somebody
already gotten there first?

00:30:38.754 --> 00:30:40.005 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Maybe.

00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:41.965 align:middle line:84%
Some have said
that our government

00:30:41.965 --> 00:30:43.175 align:middle line:90%
has reached that stage.

00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:45.677 align:middle line:90%
I don't know that we have.

00:30:45.677 --> 00:30:46.762 align:middle line:90%
But we're close.

00:30:46.762 --> 00:30:49.056 align:middle line:84%
Now, when you consider
the kinds of experiments

00:30:49.056 --> 00:30:51.558 align:middle line:84%
that are going on,
monitoring the brain activity

00:30:51.558 --> 00:30:53.852 align:middle line:90%
requires huge computing power.

00:30:53.852 --> 00:30:55.687 align:middle line:84%
This will allow it
so that you could

00:30:55.687 --> 00:30:58.690 align:middle line:84%
take those complex signals
and then generate signals just

00:30:58.690 --> 00:31:01.818 align:middle line:84%
like them and push them
into a specific individual.

00:31:01.818 --> 00:31:04.154 align:middle line:84%
This is where DARPA
has spent money

00:31:04.154 --> 00:31:06.740 align:middle line:84%
doing work for our
government researching

00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:09.868 align:middle line:84%
these very things for the
idea of training people.

00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:12.662 align:middle line:84%
So you get your training
and download of a language--

00:31:12.662 --> 00:31:15.582 align:middle line:84%
just right out of
science fiction,

00:31:15.582 --> 00:31:18.877 align:middle line:84%
where you can go and get
that kind of direct feed

00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:19.669 align:middle line:90%
into the brain.

00:31:19.669 --> 00:31:20.545 align:middle line:90%
That's what they're working on.

00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:21.755 align:middle line:90%
That's what the objective is.

00:31:21.755 --> 00:31:23.173 align:middle line:90%
That's the goal.

00:31:23.173 --> 00:31:25.133 align:middle line:84%
At the same time to
take your adversaries

00:31:25.133 --> 00:31:26.593 align:middle line:84%
and disrupt their
mental processes,

00:31:26.593 --> 00:31:28.428 align:middle line:84%
they can't even
operate the equipment

00:31:28.428 --> 00:31:31.765 align:middle line:84%
that they're responsible
for-- this is where

00:31:31.765 --> 00:31:33.433 align:middle line:90%
the sinister side pops out.

00:31:33.433 --> 00:31:36.103 align:middle line:84%
Because you can
rationalize it in one way,

00:31:36.103 --> 00:31:39.815 align:middle line:84%
but think about teaching your
kids in 30 years from now

00:31:39.815 --> 00:31:41.566 align:middle line:90%
as this technology moves down.

00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:44.236 align:middle line:84%
So you go to school, and instead
of getting a lesson that you

00:31:44.236 --> 00:31:47.781 align:middle line:90%
interact with, you get a feed.

00:31:47.781 --> 00:31:49.116 align:middle line:90%
Who controls that curriculum?

00:31:49.116 --> 00:31:50.909 align:middle line:84%
Who decides what goes
into your kid's head?

00:31:50.909 --> 00:31:50.992 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Right.

00:31:50.992 --> 00:31:53.078 align:middle line:84%
Or when you go to sleep,
they just feed it to you.

00:31:53.078 --> 00:31:55.539 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Or what about being
able to wipe out a memory

00:31:55.539 --> 00:31:56.915 align:middle line:90%
or give you a new one?

00:31:56.915 --> 00:31:59.793 align:middle line:84%
Which is the work of the
electromagnetic directorate

00:31:59.793 --> 00:32:01.461 align:middle line:84%
of the Air Force in
a publication called

00:32:01.461 --> 00:32:02.045 align:middle line:90%
"Technology Rises."

00:32:02.045 --> 00:32:03.213 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Wipe out total memory.

00:32:03.213 --> 00:32:03.463 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Yeah.

00:32:03.463 --> 00:32:04.756 align:middle line:84%
Take a memory out
and put a new one in.

00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:05.966 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Because
we are only memory.

00:32:05.966 --> 00:32:06.508 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Right.

00:32:06.508 --> 00:32:08.927 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Let's face it. if I
wake up in the morning and I

00:32:08.927 --> 00:32:11.138 align:middle line:84%
think I'm Nick Begich
and somebody has fed that

00:32:11.138 --> 00:32:12.639 align:middle line:90%
into my brain, that's who I am.

00:32:12.639 --> 00:32:13.431 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Yeah.

00:32:13.431 --> 00:32:15.016 align:middle line:84%
But think about it
from the standpoint

00:32:15.016 --> 00:32:17.102 align:middle line:90%
of evidence in a trial.

00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:17.978 align:middle line:90%
Did you see that?

00:32:17.978 --> 00:32:19.146 align:middle line:90%
Well, yeah, I saw that.

00:32:19.146 --> 00:32:21.314 align:middle line:90%
You'll swear to it.

00:32:21.314 --> 00:32:23.817 align:middle line:84%
This changes everything
about everything.

00:32:23.817 --> 00:32:27.195 align:middle line:84%
This is why it is so important
to look at these technologies

00:32:27.195 --> 00:32:30.157 align:middle line:84%
now while they're still-- I
wouldn't say in their infancy,

00:32:30.157 --> 00:32:32.951 align:middle line:84%
but they're in their
teenage years, OK?

00:32:32.951 --> 00:32:34.494 align:middle line:84%
They're a little
reckless. [CHUCKLES]

00:32:34.494 --> 00:32:35.579 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: It's kind
of frightening, Nick.

00:32:35.579 --> 00:32:36.288 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: And it is.

00:32:36.288 --> 00:32:36.913 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: It's kind
of frightening.

00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:38.081 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: It is frightening.

00:32:38.081 --> 00:32:40.625 align:middle line:84%
And at the same
time, the awareness

00:32:40.625 --> 00:32:43.295 align:middle line:84%
of it, the fact that it's
happening, become aware of it,

00:32:43.295 --> 00:32:45.964 align:middle line:84%
look at the technologies,
become more critical of them.

00:32:45.964 --> 00:32:49.134 align:middle line:84%
But the key element is
look at those things that

