00:32:58.185 --> 00:32:58.977 align:middle line:90%
level.

00:32:58.977 --> 00:33:00.854 align:middle line:84%
And then look for those
technologies that enhance that,

00:33:00.854 --> 00:33:01.730 align:middle line:90%
because they're out there.

00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:03.190 align:middle line:84%
There's light and
sound device that

00:33:03.190 --> 00:33:05.817 align:middle line:84%
can be used for enhancing
meditation, enhancing sleep,

00:33:05.817 --> 00:33:07.736 align:middle line:90%
concentration, super learning.

00:33:07.736 --> 00:33:09.571 align:middle line:84%
There's lots of
technologies that

00:33:09.571 --> 00:33:13.200 align:middle line:84%
are designed to do that so that
you can reach a better state

00:33:13.200 --> 00:33:14.826 align:middle line:84%
and then continue to
evolve [INAUDIBLE].

00:33:14.826 --> 00:33:16.828 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, let's
look at some of the neuro-

00:33:16.828 --> 00:33:21.416 align:middle line:84%
and biofeedback with
this kind of technology.

00:33:21.416 --> 00:33:24.920 align:middle line:84%
>> --And neurofeedback refer
to technology which enables us

00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:30.008 align:middle line:84%
to literally see what the
body is doing in real time.

00:33:30.008 --> 00:33:31.676 align:middle line:84%
It's like having a
mirror in which we

00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:34.012 align:middle line:84%
can see the
physiological signals

00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:37.015 align:middle line:90%
of the mind-body system.

00:33:37.015 --> 00:33:39.893 align:middle line:84%
And this enables us
to notice and learn

00:33:39.893 --> 00:33:43.939 align:middle line:84%
how to gain control over our
physiological state, our stress

00:33:43.939 --> 00:33:46.816 align:middle line:84%
levels, attention,
and performance.

00:33:49.611 --> 00:33:50.987 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I love
this technology.

00:33:50.987 --> 00:33:52.364 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Biofeedback is great.

00:33:52.364 --> 00:33:54.366 align:middle line:84%
And they're using it in
a lot of different ways.

00:33:54.366 --> 00:33:57.035 align:middle line:84%
ADD, Attention Deficit Disorder,
they're using biofeedback.

00:33:57.035 --> 00:34:00.247 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: So it does help a lot
in applications, doesn't it?

00:34:00.247 --> 00:34:02.707 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: It is so good
for so many things.

00:34:02.707 --> 00:34:04.876 align:middle line:84%
I mean, with young kids
and learning disabilities

00:34:04.876 --> 00:34:06.253 align:middle line:84%
where we're
medicating them, they

00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:08.964 align:middle line:84%
have found that if
they can take a child

00:34:08.964 --> 00:34:12.842 align:middle line:84%
in 30 to 45 one-hour sessions
with neurobiofeedback,

00:34:12.842 --> 00:34:14.844 align:middle line:84%
where they have an
interaction with a machine,

00:34:14.844 --> 00:34:16.679 align:middle line:84%
so they can get a
bouncing ball or some kind

00:34:16.679 --> 00:34:18.348 align:middle line:84%
of a visual effect,
and they learn

00:34:18.348 --> 00:34:22.601 align:middle line:84%
how to do that, within
30 to 45 sessions

00:34:22.601 --> 00:34:24.478 align:middle line:84%
they don't need
the device anymore.

00:34:24.478 --> 00:34:25.688 align:middle line:90%
They don't need the coaching.

00:34:25.688 --> 00:34:26.273 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: They're
doing it on their own.

00:34:26.273 --> 00:34:27.357 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: They've learned
how to do it on their own,

00:34:27.357 --> 00:34:30.360 align:middle line:84%
something that most of
us can't even do at will,

00:34:30.360 --> 00:34:31.860 align:middle line:84%
get right into
that learning zone.

00:34:31.860 --> 00:34:33.029 align:middle line:90%
Well, they can do it.

00:34:33.029 --> 00:34:34.697 align:middle line:84%
And they don't need
medications anymore.

00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:36.449 align:middle line:84%
They don't have things
that are destroying

00:34:36.449 --> 00:34:37.784 align:middle line:90%
the kidneys in the liver.

00:34:37.784 --> 00:34:38.994 align:middle line:90%
They're free of it.

00:34:38.994 --> 00:34:41.454 align:middle line:84%
And they're absolutely in
control of their own brain

00:34:41.454 --> 00:34:41.579 align:middle line:90%
function.

00:34:41.579 --> 00:34:43.581 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I've seen a
little kid, two years old,

00:34:43.581 --> 00:34:47.418 align:middle line:84%
playing a video game on a
smartphone that I can't even

00:34:47.418 --> 00:34:48.420 align:middle line:90%
do.

00:34:48.420 --> 00:34:49.462 align:middle line:90%
How do they do this?

00:34:49.462 --> 00:34:51.214 align:middle line:84%
Their brains are
conditioned, aren't they?

00:34:51.214 --> 00:34:53.216 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Well, and they're
younger and younger.

00:34:53.216 --> 00:34:54.926 align:middle line:84%
What's happening with
younger children is

00:34:54.926 --> 00:34:56.511 align:middle line:84%
they're getting
exposed technologies,

00:34:56.511 --> 00:34:58.722 align:middle line:84%
and they become
almost-- I mean, it's

00:34:58.722 --> 00:35:01.141 align:middle line:84%
as natural as riding
a bicycle after riding

00:35:01.141 --> 00:35:01.975 align:middle line:90%
it a couple of time.

00:35:01.975 --> 00:35:02.100 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: It's amazing.

00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:04.185 align:middle line:84%
You watch a little two-year-old
just doing their thing.

00:35:04.185 --> 00:35:05.603 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: It's
amazing to me, too.

00:35:05.603 --> 00:35:08.064 align:middle line:84%
And when you look
at the technologies,

00:35:08.064 --> 00:35:10.525 align:middle line:84%
again, in terms of
where we're headed,

00:35:10.525 --> 00:35:14.237 align:middle line:84%
the technologies are used
to damage human beings

00:35:14.237 --> 00:35:17.991 align:middle line:84%
by military planners
for obvious purposes.

00:35:17.991 --> 00:35:19.200 align:middle line:90%
That is their mission.

00:35:19.200 --> 00:35:22.078 align:middle line:84%
But the same basic
mechanisms that they discover

00:35:22.078 --> 00:35:25.665 align:middle line:84%
about human physiology and about
how the system actually works

00:35:25.665 --> 00:35:29.586 align:middle line:84%
are so valuable in the other
areas, the healing arts,

00:35:29.586 --> 00:35:32.297 align:middle line:84%
that this is where we're
losing some of that dimension.

00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:34.174 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of things
become classified,

00:35:34.174 --> 00:35:36.885 align:middle line:84%
you wait years, maybe
decades, before they finally

00:35:36.885 --> 00:35:39.220 align:middle line:84%
get released and
you can use them,

00:35:39.220 --> 00:35:40.638 align:middle line:90%
particularly in this area.

00:35:40.638 --> 00:35:44.642 align:middle line:84%
Electromedicine, the idea of
using electromagnetic fields

00:35:44.642 --> 00:35:46.644 align:middle line:84%
for effecting
health, is something

00:35:46.644 --> 00:35:49.356 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing exploding
all over the world,

00:35:49.356 --> 00:35:51.649 align:middle line:90%
more so now than ever before.

00:35:51.649 --> 00:35:54.152 align:middle line:84%
But I can go back to
the mid '80s, even,

00:35:54.152 --> 00:35:57.322 align:middle line:84%
and talk about technologies I
saw operating in Europe that

00:35:57.322 --> 00:36:02.118 align:middle line:84%
were quite amazing in this
area of electromedicine.

00:36:02.118 --> 00:36:05.080 align:middle line:84%
What we saw in the earlier
clip about the little--

00:36:05.080 --> 00:36:06.456 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Robot,
whatever it was.

00:36:06.456 --> 00:36:08.625 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: --probe, swallow
it, and it analyzes

00:36:08.625 --> 00:36:10.627 align:middle line:84%
and can dispense
medications and has cameras

00:36:10.627 --> 00:36:14.422 align:middle line:84%
and-- these are the 21st
century technologies

00:36:14.422 --> 00:36:15.632 align:middle line:90%
that we can expect to see.

00:36:15.632 --> 00:36:18.385 align:middle line:84%
And hopefully some
of these actually

00:36:18.385 --> 00:36:21.054 align:middle line:84%
drive costs down and
get visibility up

00:36:21.054 --> 00:36:23.807 align:middle line:84%
and actually head towards
curative scenarios rather than

00:36:23.807 --> 00:36:25.308 align:middle line:84%
maintenance of
symptoms scenarios

00:36:25.308 --> 00:36:27.560 align:middle line:84%
that we've seen in the
pharmaceutical direction

00:36:27.560 --> 00:36:27.852 align:middle line:90%
that we've gone.

00:36:27.852 --> 00:36:30.063 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, if it works,
it's going to work well.

00:36:30.063 --> 00:36:31.815 align:middle line:84%
But if it doesn't
or if it's abused,

00:36:31.815 --> 00:36:33.024 align:middle line:90%
it could really backfire.

00:36:33.024 --> 00:36:35.276 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: And this is it.

00:36:35.276 --> 00:36:36.820 align:middle line:84%
Like all things, I
mean, an airplane

00:36:36.820 --> 00:36:38.279 align:middle line:90%
can deliver your mail or a bomb.

00:36:38.279 --> 00:36:39.280 align:middle line:90%
Depends on the operator.

00:36:39.280 --> 00:36:40.156 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Good point.

00:36:40.156 --> 00:36:42.992 align:middle line:84%
Some questions for you have
been e-mailed in, Nick.

00:36:42.992 --> 00:36:44.994 align:middle line:84%
Benny from Salt Lake
City, how do you

00:36:44.994 --> 00:36:48.248 align:middle line:84%
feel about our government's
use of this kind of technology?

00:36:48.248 --> 00:36:50.333 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Well, I mean,
at this point it's misuse,

00:36:50.333 --> 00:36:51.709 align:middle line:90%
is probably the better phrase.

00:36:51.709 --> 00:36:57.215 align:middle line:84%
And I consider this
the most invasive area

00:36:57.215 --> 00:37:00.468 align:middle line:84%
of government
interference of anything

00:37:00.468 --> 00:37:02.512 align:middle line:84%
that we've ever
imagined, the idea

00:37:02.512 --> 00:37:04.639 align:middle line:84%
of affecting people's
free will, affecting

00:37:04.639 --> 00:37:06.099 align:middle line:84%
people's consciousness
is something

00:37:06.099 --> 00:37:09.018 align:middle line:84%
that most religious traditions
say God won't even do,

00:37:09.018 --> 00:37:11.146 align:middle line:84%
but governments think
they have a right to.

00:37:11.146 --> 00:37:14.399 align:middle line:84%
This needs to be eliminated
from the thinking

00:37:14.399 --> 00:37:15.608 align:middle line:90%
of military planners.

00:37:15.608 --> 00:37:18.695 align:middle line:84%
This is no longer and
should not be an option.

00:37:18.695 --> 00:37:19.946 align:middle line:90%
This should be a non-option.

00:37:19.946 --> 00:37:21.739 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: In a perfect
world, it should be.

00:37:21.739 --> 00:37:23.241 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Just like
blinding lasers

00:37:23.241 --> 00:37:26.077 align:middle line:84%
were decided to be a
non-option, just like using gas

00:37:26.077 --> 00:37:27.370 align:middle line:90%
in a battlefield.

00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:29.956 align:middle line:84%
And fortunately, most
times it's not used.

00:37:29.956 --> 00:37:32.208 align:middle line:84%
These are the kinds of
restrictions I'm talking about,

00:37:32.208 --> 00:37:34.752 align:middle line:84%
where at least
most of the time we

00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:37.547 align:middle line:90%
have some sort of regulation.

00:37:37.547 --> 00:37:41.843 align:middle line:84%
And I would say along with
that the penalties for misuse

00:37:41.843 --> 00:37:44.596 align:middle line:84%
ought to be hard and
severe, and there

00:37:44.596 --> 00:37:45.680 align:middle line:90%
ought to be no exemptions.

00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:46.473 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: I agree.

00:37:46.473 --> 00:37:49.517 align:middle line:84%
>>BEGICH: Because that's
where-- you cross that line,

00:37:49.517 --> 00:37:52.395 align:middle line:84%
you're crossing a line
that God won't cross.

00:37:52.395 --> 00:37:54.981 align:middle line:84%
There needs to be a penalty, and
people need to understand it.

00:37:54.981 --> 00:37:55.899 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Good point.

00:37:55.899 --> 00:37:58.193 align:middle line:84%
Shannon from
Louisville, Kentucky,

00:37:58.193 --> 00:38:01.488 align:middle line:84%
do you think there is a big
controversy going on regarding

00:38:01.488 --> 00:38:02.989 align:middle line:90%
this kind of technology?

00:38:02.989 --> 00:38:03.781 align:middle line:90%
Obviously yes.

00:38:03.781 --> 00:38:04.783 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Obviously yes.

00:38:04.783 --> 00:38:06.993 align:middle line:84%
And I think more so
now than ever before.

00:38:06.993 --> 00:38:10.788 align:middle line:84%
We were able to take this in in
the late '90s in the European

00:38:10.788 --> 00:38:12.999 align:middle line:84%
Parliament when we were
dealing with the HAARP issue.

00:38:12.999 --> 00:38:17.629 align:middle line:84%
And we got one line in
their military disarmament

00:38:17.629 --> 00:38:21.382 align:middle line:84%
and their biggest
resolution they ever passed

00:38:21.382 --> 00:38:22.884 align:middle line:90%
on military, multi-page thing.

00:38:22.884 --> 00:38:24.594 align:middle line:90%
It had five or six paragraphs.

00:38:24.594 --> 00:38:27.764 align:middle line:84%
And one was on the
manipulation of the human mind.

00:38:27.764 --> 00:38:30.433 align:middle line:84%
And the declaration
basically said, look,

00:38:30.433 --> 00:38:32.602 align:middle line:84%
we need treaty dialogue,
and we need to pursue this.

00:38:32.602 --> 00:38:34.562 align:middle line:84%
And they did through
the science directorate

00:38:34.562 --> 00:38:35.688 align:middle line:90%
of the European Parliament.

00:38:35.688 --> 00:38:37.232 align:middle line:90%
They looked into some of this.

00:38:37.232 --> 00:38:40.401 align:middle line:84%
And there is dialogue going
on at pretty high levels,

00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:41.903 align:middle line:84%
just from what
I'm familiar with.

00:38:41.903 --> 00:38:44.072 align:middle line:84%
And I know internally
in organizations,

00:38:44.072 --> 00:38:47.742 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of debate about
what's right, what's wrong.

00:38:47.742 --> 00:38:50.662 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately,
national security tends

00:38:50.662 --> 00:38:53.373 align:middle line:84%
to trump a lot of
times judgments

00:38:53.373 --> 00:38:55.458 align:middle line:84%
that other people might
make a little differently.

00:38:55.458 --> 00:38:56.834 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we see it
in our country.

00:38:56.834 --> 00:39:00.505 align:middle line:84%
We see torture, kidnapping,
extortion, blackmail.

00:39:00.505 --> 00:39:03.800 align:middle line:84%
That's our government
in operation, right?

00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:05.093 align:middle line:90%
Where do we draw the lines?

00:39:05.093 --> 00:39:08.346 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's where people
are increasingly concerned

00:39:08.346 --> 00:39:09.597 align:middle line:90%
about this area of technology.

00:39:09.597 --> 00:39:11.140 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, let's
hope it's never abused.

00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:11.850 align:middle line:90%
But it will be.

00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:13.017 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: It will be abused.

00:39:13.017 --> 00:39:14.602 align:middle line:90%
It has been abused historically.

00:39:14.602 --> 00:39:16.271 align:middle line:90%
I don't think that will stop.

00:39:16.271 --> 00:39:20.483 align:middle line:84%
In fact, even the Navy protocol
on human experimentation

00:39:20.483 --> 00:39:24.445 align:middle line:84%
that was passed in 2006--
I have it on my website.

00:39:24.445 --> 00:39:27.615 align:middle line:84%
And it says right
in there, it takes

00:39:27.615 --> 00:39:30.785 align:middle line:84%
the Deputy Secretary of
the Navy to approve them,

00:39:30.785 --> 00:39:33.288 align:middle line:84%
but they still have
the right to approve--

00:39:33.288 --> 00:39:34.706 align:middle line:84%
and they say that
in these words--

00:39:34.706 --> 00:39:36.165 align:middle line:90%
mind control experiments.

00:39:36.165 --> 00:39:38.334 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Nick, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief."

00:39:38.334 --> 00:39:39.419 align:middle line:90%
>>BEGICH: Thanks for having me.

00:39:39.419 --> 00:39:41.546 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: It's called
"Controlling the Human Mind."

00:39:41.546 --> 00:39:44.090 align:middle line:90%
It's been going on for years.

00:39:44.090 --> 00:39:46.551 align:middle line:84%
And more and more of
this is going to happen.

00:39:46.551 --> 00:39:50.513 align:middle line:84%
But you need to be aware of it
so you can fight back and not

00:39:50.513 --> 00:39:54.100 align:middle line:84%
let it happen to you so when
you wake up in the morning,

00:39:54.100 --> 00:39:57.020 align:middle line:84%
you remember
exactly who you are.

00:39:57.020 --> 00:40:00.064 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory, and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief."

